INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (54,148,'Robert Williams','robwilliamsgd@gmail.com','http://robertwilliams.wpengine.com','72.199.110.121','2013-05-27 00:26:54','2013-05-27 00:26:54','Sure, some of the leads (especially on folyo) would reply saying something like, \"Hey thanks, but we chose another designer - I\'ll keep you in mind for future projects.\" \n\nI simply replied to the email saying \"Is it ok if I follow up with you about the project in a month?\" most would say yes. I put them in a seperate folder in my email.\n\nThen I simply followed up in a few months with something like, \"Hi how are you? you mentioned you wanted me to follow up, your project seemed interesting how is it going?\"',0,'0','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_3) AppleWebKit/537.31 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/26.0.1410.65 Safari/537.31','',52,2);
